Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Combine peanut butter, water, soy sauce, vinegar and ginger in small bowl; stir until smooth. Place pizza crust on foil-lined baking sheet. Spread peanut butter mixture evenly over pizza crust. Sprinkle cheese, chicken, edamame, bell peppers and chow men noodles evenly over crust. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until cheese is melted. Cut into 8 slices and serve.